Christmas came early, folks! Jack Parow and Jitsvinger released their track, Dis Bef*k Remix (censored version is called Dis Bfk Remix), free of charge on Thursday. The track was originally released on the acoustic side of Parow s double album, Nag van die Lang Pette (2014), and is about his love for his daughter, Ruby. The release coincides with something adorable the footage for the music video was taken by none other than Ruby. She was fitted with a GoPro so that the video portrays life from her perspective. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.